item.title: Compiler Problem
item.dc:creator: @Tom Tom
item.description:
@Tom wrote:

[quote=“Epicskillz, post:11, topic:340952”][quote author=TOMSCAPE BETA link=topic=437346.msg3213792#msg3213792 date=1274519805]

I Changed it to *.class and it says everything is an invalid flag.

No…

Compiled can’t compile Java byte code, they compile Java code into Java byte code so your server can read it and work, you need to compile the Java files, not the .class.

Just move the .java files near your compiler as I’ve said before, if there isn’t any Java files then de-compile the class files using the below link.

http://download.cnet.com/DJ-Java-Decompiler/3000-2213_4-10046809.html

K,I Have 1 error though after removing an antileech

server.java:151: cannot find symbol symbol : methos banhost(java.lang.String.int) location: class server

Uh just post the code, on line 151. I don’t wana tell you the wrong thing, good to be sure than sorry. (server.java)
[/quote]

Ok , thank you very much also , I cant find whats wrong;

} if (num > 5) { banHost(host, num); return false; }[/quote]

Change ‘banHost’ to ‘banhost’. I believe they’re something wrong with one of the banhost things, not the actual code but they way it’s being put. Don’t hold me on that thought, I have a growing feeling I maybe wrong…

I Have Lol, Im Not Stupid… Also I Know that there is a sticky for this but it will never get answered there…

javac: file not found: *.java
